comments.body:
styling tiny nit:

In case you like it:
```c++
// Mark all already spent inputs, and all txs that consumes them, as conflicted
for (auto range = mapTxSpends.equal_range(tx_in.prevout); range.first != range.second; range.first++) {
    const uint256& spent_id = range.first->second;
    // Skip the recently added tx
    if (spent_id == conflict_txid) continue;
    RecursiveUpdateTxState(/*batch=*/nullptr, spent_id, [&conflict_txid](CWalletTx& wtx) EXCLUSIVE_LOCKS_REQUIRED(cs_wallet) {
    	return wtx.mempool_conflicts.insert(conflict_txid).second ? TxUpdate::CHANGED : TxUpdate::UNCHANGED;
    });
}
```

(same for `transactionRemovedFromMempool`)

